---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
export const prerender = true;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="Thomas Dvornik, Principal Engineer at Salesforce. 15 years building platforms, CLIs, and AI systems. Marin, CA."
>
  <div class="page">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="hero-section">
        <div class="hero-text">
          <span class="label">About</span>
          <h1>Thomas Dvornik.</h1>
          <p class="tagline">Principal Engineer · Marin, CA · 15 years at Salesforce</p>
          <p class="hero-quote">
            "My passion is building products that customers love (platforms,
            developer tools, productivity) and finding the right balance between
            moving fast and moving safe."
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-photo">
          <img
            src="/thomas.jpg"
            alt="Thomas Dvornik"
            class="photo"
            width="340"
            height="420"
          />
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">15+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">years at Salesforce</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">30M+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">monthly CLI executions at handoff</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">400+</div>
          <div class="stat-label">OSS contributions</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-number">4.71</div>
          <div class="stat-label">Dreamforce speaker rating</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="currently">
        <h2 class="section-label">Currently thinking about</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Where AI actually pays off in enterprise developer tooling vs. where it's noise</li>
          <li>Multi-tenant business architecture: the hard parts (residency, billing hierarchy, org lifecycle)</li>
          <li>The gap between AI demo and AI product at enterprise scale</li>
          <li>Edge computing and the Cloudflare Workers primitives I wish existed three years ago</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="bio">
        <h2 class="section-label">Background</h2>
        <p>
          I've always been drawn to building things. It started with computers.
          My brother and I would pull machines apart and put them back together,
          mostly to run games, often all night. My sister taught me HTML. In high
          school I found robotics through FIRST competitions, traveling the country
          doing mechanical design, firmware, and running onto the field mid-match
          to fix whatever broke (I was always the one who had to run out).
        </p>
        <p>
          I got my Bachelor's and Master's in Computer Science at
          <strong>Cal Poly San Luis Obispo</strong>. My thesis was on building a
          browser-based <a href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/5876137" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="inline-link">WebIDE</a>
          to help entry-level students learn to program, removing environment
          setup as a barrier and baking in best practices from day one. That was
          before cloud IDEs were a normal thing to do. The paper made it into
          IEEE. I was a founding member of the Eta Delta chapter of
          <strong>Sigma Pi</strong> and led orientation groups for incoming
          students.
        </p>
        <p>
          In 2008 I joined Salesforce as an intern and never really left. Over
          fifteen years I've built things that are still in production: the
          <strong>Developer Console</strong> (Salesforce's in-browser Apex IDE,
          still widely used a decade later even though the stack around it has
          moved on) and the <strong>Setup tree</strong> (the left-rail navigation
          every Salesforce admin uses, and by interaction count the most-touched
          single component in Setup). In between I co-founded
          <strong>HearNow Technologies</strong> as CTO, an IoT notification
          platform in Node.js, AWS, and Twilio, and won two internal Salesforce
          hack days.
        </p>
        <p>
          The chapter I'm proudest of is the Salesforce DX era. I architected the
          <strong>Salesforce CLI</strong> from conception to over
          <strong>30 million executions a month</strong>: 130+ commands, 60+
          external plugins, 4,000+ automated tests across OS and shell matrix. I
          was a trusted committer on the <strong>oclif</strong> open-source
          framework and spoke at Dreamforce 2019 (two sessions, 262 attendees,
          4.35-4.71 ratings, 1,295 bookmarks), TrailheaDX, and oclifconf.
        </p>
        <p>
          Since 2023 I've been leading engineering on Salesforce's Digital Wallet:
          consumption metering, billing infrastructure, and an agentic AI
          experience that lets sellers query their usage data in plain English. I'm
          also the AI Champion for my org, driving agentic tooling into the
          engineering workflow and building the skills and hooks that make
          that real.
        </p>
        <p>
          I live in Marin with my wife Justine and our three kids.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="timeline">
        <h2 class="section-label">Career</h2>
        <div class="timeline-items">
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <div class="timeline-meta">
                <span class="company">Salesforce</span>
                <span class="period">2016 – Present</span>
              </div>
              <div class="role">Principal Member of Technical Staff</div>
              <p>
                Salesforce DX CLI lead → Digital Wallet engineering lead. Built
                the CLI from zero to 30M+ monthly executions. Now leading
                multi-tenant consumption architecture and an agentic AI
                experience for sellers.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <div class="timeline-meta">
                <span class="company">HearNow Technologies</span>
                <span class="period">2015 – 2016</span>
              </div>
              <div class="role">Co-Founder & CTO</div>
              <p>
                IoT notification platform from scratch: Node.js, Express, MongoDB,
                Twilio, AWS. Investor demos, device-to-service firmware integration.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="timeline-item">
            <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
            <div class="timeline-content">
              <div class="timeline-meta">
                <span class="company">Salesforce</span>
                <span class="period">2008 – 2015</span>
              </div>
              <div class="role">Intern → Associate MTS → Lead MTS</div>
              <p>
                Built the Developer Console and the Setup tree. Won two internal
                hack days. This was the first chapter of my Salesforce career.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="connect">
        <h2 class="section-label">Connect</h2>
        <div class="links">
          <a
            href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/thomasdvornik/"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="connect-link">LinkedIn</a>
          <a
            href="https://github.com/amphro"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="connect-link">GitHub</a>
          <a
            href="https://ieeexplore.ieee.org/document/5876137"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer"
            class="connect-link">IEEE Publication</a>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page {
    padding: 8rem max(1.5rem, 4vw) 6rem;
  }

  .container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4rem;
  }

  /* ── Hero section ── */
  .hero-section {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr auto;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .hero-section {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .hero-photo {
      order: -1;
    }
  }

  .label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0.3rem 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .tagline {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .hero-quote {
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--text);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0 0 0.25rem;
    font-style: italic;
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .hero-quote-source {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    margin: 0;
    opacity: 0.6;
  }

  .photo {
    width: 280px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 12px;
    object-fit: cover;
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    display: block;
    filter: contrast(1.02) saturate(0.95);
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .photo {
      width: 160px;
    }
  }

  /* ── Bio ── */
  .bio {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .bio p {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--text);
    margin: 0;
    opacity: 0.85;
  }

  .bio strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
    opacity: 1;
  }

  .inline-link {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 40%, transparent);
    transition: border-color 0.15s ease;
  }

  .inline-link:hover {
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* ── Stats ── */
  .stats-row {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
    gap: 1px;
    background: var(--border);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .stats-row {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  .stat {
    background: var(--surface);
    padding: 1.5rem 1.25rem;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.25rem;
  }

  .stat-number {
    font-size: 1.75rem;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--accent);
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .stat-label {
    font-size: 0.72rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }

  /* ── Section label ── */
  .section-label {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--accent);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  /* ── Currently ── */
  .currently ul {
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
  }

  .currently li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    line-height: 1.6;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .currently li::before {
    content: '—';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--accent);
  }

  /* ── Timeline ── */
  .timeline-items {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 1.75rem;
  }

  .timeline-item {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .timeline-dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
    margin-top: 0.45rem;
  }

  .timeline-content {
    flex: 1;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.3rem;
  }

  .timeline-meta {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .company {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--text);
  }

  .period {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
  }

  .role {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--muted);
  }

  .timeline-content p {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--muted);
    margin: 0.4rem 0 0;
  }

  /* ── Connect ── */
  .links {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .connect-link {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--muted);
    text-decoration: none;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    padding-bottom: 2px;
    transition: color 0.2s ease, border-color 0.2s ease;
  }

  .connect-link:hover {
    color: var(--accent);
    border-color: var(--accent);
  }
</style>
